headline: Chipotle stock tumbles on same-store sales miss
summary: Chipotle Mexican Grill (CMG) reported second quarter adjusted earnings that were in line with Wall Street expectations of $0.33 per share. Revenue of $3.06 billion was short of the expected $3.11 billion. Same-store sales fell 4% versus a Bloomberg consensus estimate of a 2.9% decline. Yahoo Finance Senior Reporter Brooke DiPalma breaks down the results. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Asking for a Trend here.

headline: Chipotle Earnings: Another Rough Quarter
summary: Chipotle missed revenue expectations as comparable-restaurant sales fell 4% in the second quarter.  Chipotle managed to eke out 3% revenue growth in the second quarter, below analyst expectations, only because it opened 61 new company-owned restaurants.  Adjusted earnings per share was down slightly, while operating margin contracted by 1.5 percentage points to 18.2%.

headline: Comparable sales drop undermines Chipotle’s margin gains, stock falls
summary: Investing.com -- Shares of Chipotle Mexican Grill Inc (NYSE:CMG) fell sharply Wednesday after the burrito chain delivered a mixed second-quarter performance and issued a muted sales outlook for the full year. Despite adjusted earnings per share of $0.33 narrowly beating Wall Street estimates, investors focused on a drop in comparable sales and a dour forecast, sending the stock down 8.7% after-hours.

headline: Chipotle cuts annual sales target as dining out slows; shares drop
summary: (Reuters) -Chipotle Mexican Grill on Wednesday lowered its annual sales growth target again and missed quarterly sales estimates as economic uncertainty prompts Americans to dine out less, sending the burrito chain's shares down 9.7% after hours.  Companies are also taking stock of President Donald Trump's tariff policy that could lead to higher supply chain costs and further pressure consumer spending.  Chipotle now expects annual comparable restaurant sales to be about flat year-over-year, while its prior target was for growth in the low single-digit range.
